metadata.metaValue: This compound creates the **Robot.usd** layer that is referenced in **RobotScene.usd**.
This compound creates the **RobotScene.usd** layer. Two "robots" (some simple spheres actually) are using the metal materials.
# This graph setup is similar to the *Specializes* example of the OpenUSD Glossary
Implements the "Specializes" example from the Open USD glossary webpage
Define our base metal material.  We author the **diffuse_color** and **roughness** attribute of a **UsdPreviewSurface** shader.
Since *CorrodedMetal* prim *specializes* the *Metal* prim, it  has the strongest opinion for its **roughness** and **metallic** attributes.

We override the **diffuseColor** and **roughness** attributes on the **Metal** material  but the **CorrodedMetal** (assigned to *RustedBall*) is affected only by the **diffuseColor** override as its **rougness** is specialized in **Robot.usd**.
Define two balls bellow the geo prim
Add */World/Characters/Rosie* to the stage. */Rosie* prim is referencing *Robot.usd*
